"title": "4538: vineyard",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "4538: vineyard",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>A cultivated field or garden, sometimes surrounded by a wall, in which vines and other trees were grown. Israel is sometimes compared to a vineyard. Some of Jesus Christ's parables concern vineyards.</p>\n<h2>Vineyards were sometimes surrounded by walls</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt21:33\">MAT 21:33</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark12:1\">MRK 12:1</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num22:24\">NUM 22:24</a></p>\n<h2>Vineyards were associated with a settled, peaceful life</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa65:20-Isa65:22\">ISA 65:20–65:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen9:20\">GEN 9:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut6:10-Deut6:11\">DEU 6:10–6:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs18:31-2Kgs18:32\">2KI 18:31–18:32</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa36:16-Isa36:17\">ISA 36:16–36:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs19:29\">2KI 19:29</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa37:30\">ISA 37:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr26:10\">2CH 26:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh9:25\">NEH 9:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps107:37-Ps107:38\">PSA 107:37–107:38</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song7:12\">SNG 7:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer31:3-Jer31:5\">JER 31:3–31:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer32:15\">JER 32:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer35:6-Jer35:10\">JER 35:6–35:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek28:26\">EZK 28:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos9:14\">AMO 9:14</a></p>\n<h2>Vineyards were important for agriculture</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs25:11-2Kgs25:12\">2KI 25:11–25:12</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer39:9-Jer39:10\">JER 39:9–39:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer52:15-Jer52:16\">JER 52:15–52:16</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num20:17\">NUM 20:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num21:22\">NUM 21:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut20:6\">DEU 20:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg14:5\">JDG 14:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg15:4-Judg15:5\">JDG 15:4–15:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam8:10-1Sam8:14\">1SA 8:10–8:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr27:27\">1CH 27:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh5:1-Neh5:5\">NEH 5:1–5:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh5:11\">NEH 5:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa61:5\">ISA 61:5</a></p>\n<h2>Vineyards were a sign of wealth</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam22:7\">1SA 22:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs5:26\">2KI 5:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov31:16\">PRO 31:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl2:4\">ECC 2:4</a></p>\n<h2>Regulations relating to vineyards</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev19:10\">LEV 19:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod22:5\">EXO 22:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod23:11\">EXO 23:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev25:3-Lev25:4\">LEV 25:3–25:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut22:9\">DEU 22:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut23:24\">DEU 23:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut24:21\">DEU 24:21</a></p>\n<h2>The produce of vineyards not enjoyed by owner</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut28:39\">DEU 28:39</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut28:30\">DEU 28:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos5:11\">AMO 5:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zeph1:13\">ZEP 1:13</a></p>\n<h2>Naboth's vineyard</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs21:1-1Kgs21:19\">1KI 21:1–21:19</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Vineyards in parables</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt21:28-Matt21:32\">MAT 21:28–21:32</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song8:11-Song8:12\">SNG 8:11–8:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt20:1-Matt20:16\">MAT 20:1–20:16</a> <em>the parable of the workers in the vineyard</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt21:33-Matt21:44\">MAT 21:33–21:44</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark12:1-Mark12:11\">MRK 12:1–12:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke20:9-Luke20:18\">LUK 20:9–20:18</a> <em>the parable of the tenants</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke13:6-Luke13:9\">LUK 13:6–13:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor9:7\">1CO 9:7</a></p>\n<h2>The metaphorical use of vineyards</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek19:10\">EZK 19:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job24:6\">JOB 24:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song1:14\">SNG 1:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song2:15\">SNG 2:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa3:14\">ISA 3:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa5:1-Isa5:7\">ISA 5:1–5:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer12:10\">JER 12:10</a></p>",
